  "text": "HomeShoppingLaunched in 2021, Beia's personal body-care offerings are available at Free People and Urban Outfitters.Brittany Lo, founder of Beia.Photo: Courtesy of BeiaBrand Bio is Fashionista's guide to the best independent fashion and beauty brands — a resource for retailers, job seekers, B2B companies and consumers alike. If you'd like your brand to be featured, fill out this form.BeiaHeadquarters: New York, NYE-commerce: beiabeauty.com Social Media: Instagram / TikTok / FacebookWhat: A personal body-care brand combining skin care with intimate wellness via a serum, setting spray, body scrub and pH-balanced wipes.Price Range: $20-$48Founder: Brittany Lo. She is also the founder of Beautini, a bridal beauty company offering hair and makeup services.Origin Story: Lo first got her start on the beauty side of the wedding industry with her company Beautini. After learning that skin-care concerns in intimate areas can affect women's confidence, she launched Beia in 2021. Beia — which was named for the Chinese word \"bao bei\" (寶貝), meaning \"precious treasure\" — aims to address odor, sweat and body blemishes in intimate areas \"in an elevated, luxurious way so that you can feel your best self, look your best self, and be your best self.\" The vegan body-care brand currently offers four SKUs all priced below $50.Scroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesPhoto: Courtesy of BeiaStockists: Free People, Urban Outfitters, AmazonHero Products: Body \u0026 Intimacy Serum ($42), Refresh Wipes ($20), Daily Hydrating \u0026 Setting Mist ($48), Bikini \u0026 Body Scrub ($38)PR Representation: Brittany MarshakHow to get in touch: Contact FormWant your brand featured? Hit the link below.Please note: Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. This in no way affects our editorial decision-making.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
